100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On February 3, 1926, the League of Nations held discussions in Geneva to address the growing tensions in Europe, particularly concerning disarmament efforts amid rising militarism. In the United States, the Ford Motor Company announced plans to expand its production, signaling optimism in the post-war economy. Meanwhile, in China, revolutionary factions continued to clash, raising concerns over stability in the region.
